# Copy this file to .env and set your preferred folder paths.
# If omitted, intake defaults to ./intake and output to ./output
# (relative to the directory where you run docker-compose).

# INTAKE_PATH=/Users/yourname/Desktop/receipts
# OUTPUT_PATH=/Users/yourname/Documents/reimbursements-output

# Optional shared-secret auth. Leave unset for an open localhost install. When
# set, every request must present this token (header X-Auth-Token, an auth_token
# cookie, or open the page once with ?token=<value>). Set this before exposing
# the app beyond 127.0.0.1.
# APP_AUTH_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-string

# Where the SMTP password / Dropbox token (and the cloud LLM API keys below) are
# stored. Defaults to a LOCAL (non cloud-synced) volume in Docker; never point
# this inside OUTPUT_PATH.
# SECRETS_PATH=/data/config/secrets.json

# ── OpenRouter cloud provider (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Use OpenRouter's cloud API instead of a local LLM. Heads-up: this sends receipt
# data off your machine, so it's opt-in — pick "OpenRouter" in Settings → AI Model
# (the free router "openrouter/free" is the default there, steered toward quick,
# reliable, vision-capable FREE models). Prefer "Send OCR text only" to keep the
# receipt IMAGE local.
#
# Set your key ONE of these ways (do NOT commit it — this file is a template):
#   • Settings → AI Model → OpenRouter → "OpenRouter API key" (stored in the local
#     .app_secrets.json — recommended), or
#   • this env var / your own .env (which is gitignored):
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
#
# Zero-click: if OPENROUTER_API_KEY is set on a FRESH install (no provider chosen
# yet), the app auto-selects the OpenRouter free router on first run. It never
# overrides a choice you've already made.

# ── Bundled LLM (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Run a local model INSIDE Docker instead of an external LM Studio. Two ways:
#
# A) Use the bundled-variant preset (recommended) — copy .env.bundled.example to
#    .env, then:
#      docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.bundled.yml up --build
#    (The "lite" preset, .env.lite.example + docker-compose.lite.yml, NEVER bundles
#    a model — it uses a host LM Studio or OpenRouter. See README "Choosing a build".)
#
# B) Manually, with the profile + URL:
#
#   LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL=http://model-server:1234/v1 \
#     docker compose --profile bundled-llm up --build
#
# The weights are baked into the model-server image (offline at runtime). The
# default bundled model is unsloth's Qwen3-VL-2B-Instruct (UD-Q5_K_XL) — a small
# vision model — with its F16 vision projector (mmproj). You only need to set
# LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL to use it; MODEL_URL / MMPROJ_URL are optional overrides for
# baking in a different GGUF + mmproj.
# LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL=http://model-server:1234/v1
# MODEL_URL=https://huggingface.co/unsloth/Qwen3-VL-2B-Instruct-GGUF/resolve/main/Qwen3-VL-2B-Instruct-UD-Q5_K_XL.gguf
# MMPROJ_URL=https://huggingface.co/unsloth/Qwen3-VL-2B-Instruct-GGUF/resolve/main/mmproj-F16.gguf

# ── Multi-user mode (ON by default) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Multi-user is now the DEFAULT: several people can share ONE instance, each with a
# private board, results, reports, folders and run-log they can't see across.
# Sign-in is local username/password (pbkdf2-hashed, signed HttpOnly session
# cookie) — no external auth service. The first visit offers a one-time "create the
# first admin" step; admins manage everyone else from Settings → Users.
#
# Opt OUT for a classic single-user, no-login install:
# MULTIUSER_ENABLED=false
#
# Seed the first admin on a fresh box (skips the create-first-account screen).
# Both must be set to seed.
# MULTIUSER_ADMIN_USER=admin
# MULTIUSER_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me-please
#
# Session/security knobs (sane defaults; override only if you need to):
# SESSION_TTL_SECS=2592000        # how long a sign-in lasts (default 30 days)
# PBKDF2_ITERATIONS=240000        # password-hash work factor
# SESSION_SECRET=                 # HMAC signing key; auto-generated + stored in
#                                 # .app_secrets.json if unset (leave blank)

# ── Email intake (inbound IMAP receipts) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Forward receipts (any vendor) to a dedicated mailbox and the app pulls them in
# automatically. Configure it in Settings → Email Intake (host/user/App Password,
# stored in .app_secrets.json). Gmail: enable 2-Step Verification + IMAP, then
# generate a 16-char App Password — no Google Cloud project or approvals needed.
# IMAP_PASSWORD=                  # optional: app password via env instead of UI
# IMAP_TIMEOUT=20                 # seconds before an unreachable host fails fast
# EMAIL_RENDER_FALLBACK=false     # optional: render HTML e-receipts to an image
#                                 # and OCR them when body-text distillation fails
#                                 # (needs imgkit + wkhtmltoimage installed)

# ── Google Drive intake (opt-in cloud capture source) ────────────────────────
# Poll a Google Drive "receipts inbox" folder and download new image/PDF files
# into the pipeline. Off by default; configure it in Settings → Google Drive
# Intake (folder ID + a one-time Google OAuth consent). Needs google-api-python-
# client + google-auth-oauthlib (in requirements.txt). The OAuth refresh token +
# client secret live in .app_secrets.json (never the synced config). See
# GOOGLE_DRIVE_IMPORT.md + GMAIL_TO_DRIVE_SETUP.md.
# GDRIVE_CLIENT_SECRET=           # optional: OAuth client secret via env instead of UI
# GDRIVE_REFRESH_TOKEN=           # optional: pre-obtained refresh token via env
# GDRIVE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost  # OAuth installed-app redirect for consent
# GDRIVE_TIMEOUT=30               # seconds before an unreachable Drive call fails fast
